Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper is primarily focused on the control of robotic systems, specifically the adaptive control of robotic systems with an inner/outer loop structure. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the control of dynamic systems, specifically robotic systems, and proposes a modularity approach to resolve the issue of existing outer loop controllers not taking into consideration the dynamic effects of robots. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a class of adaptive outer loop control schemes for robotic systems, which may involve machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes adaptive control schemes for robotic systems, which may involve artificial intelligence techniques. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects related to the implementation of the proposed adaptive control schemes for robotic systems.
